            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "Most heater manufacturers require documented annual professional maintenance to maintain warranty coverage—skipping maintenance can void warranties worth thousands of dollars. Modern high-efficiency furnaces and heat pumps come with 10-year parts warranties (sometimes extended to 12 years with registration), but these warranties specifically require proof of annual service by licensed HVAC professionals. If a $1,200 heat exchanger or $2,400 compressor fails during warranty period, manufacturers will deny claims if you cannot provide service records showing annual maintenance. Our ServiceTitan electronic documentation automatically maintains your complete service history, photographs of system condition, combustion analysis results, and technician notes—creating bulletproof warranty compliance records. For a $6,500 heater with 10-year parts warranty, annual $150 service protecting $6,500 in warranty coverage represents outstanding insurance value. Even one major warranty-covered repair ($1,000-$3,500 saved) justifies years of maintenance costs. Professional service also identifies developing problems during warranty periods, enabling warranty-covered repairs before expiration—maximizing manufacturer obligation rather than paying out-of-pocket after warranty expires. Documented maintenance increases home resale value by demonstrating responsible ownership and system care, often adding $500-$1,500 to sale price or expediting buyer decisions by reducing concerns about deferred maintenance or hidden mechanical problems."
